2) F) Answer the following questions using the verb potential form in the negative : 
  1) too spicy =  iie, kara sugi de taberare masen deshita
  2) too difficult = iie, muzukashi sugi te de ki masen deshita 
  3) too hot = iie, atsu sugi te haire masen deshita 
  4) too busy = iie, isogashi sugi te dekake rare masen deshita 
  5) too many = iie, oo sugi te oboerare masen deshita 
  6) too cold = iie, samu sugi te oyoge masen deshita 
2) G) Group activity "What is it?" game : 
II) A) Answer the questions using ~Shi ~Shi. Examine the ideas and cues, and decide whether to use +affirmative or -negative :
  1) konshuu wa isogashi desu ka? = this week busy? = shiken ga arushi, shukudai ga takusan meru shi, isogashii desu
  2) atarashi apa-to wa ii desu ka? = new appartment good? = kuukou ni chikai shi, benrida shi, ii desu
  3) keisai no shugiyou o tori masu ka? = sensei wa kibishii shi, nagai repoto- o kakanaki yaikenai shi, torimasen
  4) ryokou wa tanoshi ka-ta desu ka? = tabemono ga oishi kuna ka-ta shi, kotoba ga wakara naka-ta shi, tanoshi kuna ka-ta desu
  5) konban, pa-ti- ni iki masu ka? = tonight party go? = chouto kibun ga warui shi, kiinoumo pa-ti- ni ita shi, ikimasen
  6) nihongo no shinbun ga yome masu ka? = japanese newspaper read? = kanji ga yomenai shi, bunbou ga wakaranai shi, yomemasen 
  7) hitori de ryokou ga deki masu ka? = nihongo ga hanaseru shi, mouoto nada shi, dekimasu
  8) tanaka san ga suki desu ka? = uso o tsuku shi, yakusoku o mamo ranai shi, suki janai desu
